verbose_text: Previous studies revealed that hypoxia inducible factor-1, mitogen activated protein kinase, transforming growth factor-beta (TGF-beta), fibroblast grow factor-2 (FGF2), osteopontin, macrophage migration inhibitory factor and 15-lipoxygenase (15-LO) are associated with the hypoxia induced proliferation, migration, protein synthesis and phenotypic change behav-iors of PAFs.
evidence: hypoxia inducible factor-1, mitogen activated protein kinase, transforming growth factor-beta
